### Ingredients

<RecipeIngredients>
  <>2 cups all-purpose flour</>
  <>2 tablespoons sugar</>
  <>2 teaspoons baking powder</>
  <>1 teaspoon salt</>
  <>2 large eggs</>
  <>1 3/4 cups milk</>
  <>1/4 cup melted butter</>
  <>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</>
  <>Butter for cooking</>
  <>Heat a griddle or large skillet over medium heat and brush with butter</>
  <>Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto the hot griddle</>
  <>Cook until bubbles form on surface and edges look set, about 2-3 minutes</>
  <>Flip and cook until golden brown on other side, 1-2 minutes more</>
</RecipeIngredients>

### Instructions

<InstructionsContainer>
  <InstructionsSection title="Prepare Batter">
    <InstructionStep stepNumber={1}>
      In a <strong>large</strong> bowl, whisk together <strong>flour</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>baking</strong> <strong>powder</strong>, and <strong>salt</strong>
    </InstructionStep>

    <InstructionStep stepNumber={2}>
      In another bowl, beat <strong>eggs</strong> then whisk in <strong>milk</strong>, <strong>melted</strong> <strong>butter</strong>, and <strong>vanilla</strong>
    </InstructionStep>
  </InstructionsSection>
</InstructionsContainer>

### Notes

<RecipeNotes>
  <>Don't overmix the batter - lumps are okay</>
  <>Let batter rest for 5 minutes before cooking for fluffier pancakes</>
  <>Serve immediately with maple syrup and butter</>
  <>Leftover pancakes can be frozen for up to 3 months</>
</RecipeNotes>

